eged that the defendant stole the phone belonging to one Amos Adeyei. “The defendant stole the complainant’s phone and converted it to his own. “After it was discovered that the defendant was the culprit, he was arrested. “The phone was recovered from him.” Ayorinde noted that the offence violates Section 287 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the section stipulates three years imprisonment for stealing. The case was adjourned until March 16 for mention. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria By Jane Echewodo A security guard, Nasiru Abubakar, yesterday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court, for allegedly stealing $8,000 and a cell phone, properties of an expatriate, Mrs Iryna Dubuchenko. Abubakar, who lives in Mobolaji Bank Anthony Way in Ikeja, is answering questions on one count charge of stealing before… August 22, 2019 In "News" A Magistrates’ Court in Ikorodu, Lagos State, on Friday sentenced an unemployed man, Tunde Olushola, to nine months imprisonment with hard labour for breaking a Hyundai Creta Jeep windshield. Magistrate A.R. Onilogbo, sentenced Olushola based on the convict’s confession and evidence that broke the windshield of a Hyundai Creta Jeep… March 20, 2020 In "Metro" A 27-year-old man, Oluwatosin Olapade, has been arraigned before an Ikeja Magistrate Court, Lagos, over alleged rape and stealing of phones. September 17, 2013 In "News"